{
    "summary": "Bulk update __VAR:entity_plural__",
    "description": "Updates multiple __VAR:entity_singular__ records in a single request.\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis endpoint allows you to **update multiple records simultaneously**, which is more efficient than making individual update requests. This is useful for:\n\n- **Batch operations**: Update multiple records with different values in one request\n- **Performance optimization**: Reduce API calls when updating many records\n- **Atomic operations**: All updates succeed or fail together (depending on implementation)\n\n---\n\n## Model Information\n\n### Updatable Fields\n__VAR:fields_description__\n\n### Available Relations\n__VAR:relations_description__\n\n---\n\n## Request Format\n\nThe request body must contain an object with the model key (lowercase plural) containing an array of objects:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"__VAR:entity_url__\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"status\": \"shipped\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"status\": \"shipped\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"status\": \"delivered\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `id` | integer | **Yes** | The unique identifier of the record to update |\n| `...fields` | mixed | No | Any updatable field from the model |\n\n---\n\n## Response Format\n\n**Success:**\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"models\": [\n    {\n      \"success\": true,\n      \"model\": {...}\n    },\n    {\n      \"success\": true,\n      \"model\": {...}\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Partial Failure:**\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": false,\n  \"models\": [\n    {\"success\": true, \"model\": {...}},\n    {\"success\": false, \"errors\": {\"field\": [\"Error message\"]}}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Validation Rules\n\nEach item in the array must comply with the following validation rules:\n\n__VAR:validation_description__\n\n---\n\n## Behavior\n\n| Aspect | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| **Transaction** | All updates are wrapped in a database transaction |\n| **Atomicity** | If one update fails, all changes are rolled back |\n| **Response** | Returns all updated records or detailed error information |\n| **Partial Updates** | Only provided fields are updated (PATCH behavior) |",
    "tags": [
        "__VAR:module__"
    ],
    "requestBody": {
        "required": true,
        "description": "Object containing the model key with array of __VAR:entity_singular__ objects to update. Each object must include the `id` field.",
        "content": {
            "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "__VAR:entity_url__": {
                            "type": "array",
                            "minItems": 1,
                            "description": "Array of __VAR:entity_singular__ objects to update",
                            "items": {
                                "type": "object",
                                "required": ["id"],
                                "properties": {
                                    "id": {
                                        "type": "integer",
                                        "description": "Unique identifier of the record to update"
                                    }
                                },
                                "additionalProperties": true
                            }
                        }
                    },
                    "required": ["__VAR:entity_url__"]
                },
                "example": {
                    "__VAR:entity_url__": [
                        {
                            "id": 101,
                            "status": "shipped"
                        },
                        {
                            "id": 102,
                            "status": "shipped"
                        },
                        {
                            "id": 103,
                            "status": "delivered"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            }
        }
    },
    "responses": {
